'''Kose Clan''' (巨勢氏) is a {{ill|clan|de|Clan|ja|氏族|qq=draft}} that adopts “Kose” as its clan name.

It was an {{ill|Ancient|de|Antik|ja|古代|qq=draft}} {{ill|Powerful Clan|de|Einflussreiche Familie|ja|豪族|qq=draft}} based in {{ill|Yamato Province|de|Yamato Provinz|ja|大和国|qq=draft}}{{ill|Takaichi District|de|Takaichi Bezirk|ja|高市郡|qq=draft}}Kose District (巨勢郷) (present‐day {{ill|Nara Prefecture|de|Nara-Präfektur|ja|奈良県|qq=draft}}{{ill|Gose City|de|Gose Stadt|ja|御所市|qq=draft}} Furuse (古瀬)){{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2310}}. The orthography of “Kose” is attested as '''Kose''' (許勢), , '''Kose''' (居勢), and {{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2310}}. The {{ill|Kabane|de|Kabane|ja|カバネ|lt=Surname|lt_ja=姓|lt_de=Familienname|qq=draft}} was originally read as {{reading|{{ill|Omi|de|Omi|ja|臣|qq=draft}}|o‑mi}}, and in the 13th year of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|de|Kaiser Tenmu|ja|天武天皇|qq=draft}} ({{ill|684 AD|de|684 AD|ja|684年|qq=draft}}), with the establishment of the {{ill|Eight Family Names|de|Acht Familiennamen|ja|八色の姓|qq=draft}}, it was changed to the surname {{ill|Asomi|de|Asomi|ja|朝臣|qq=draft}}{{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2311}}.

== Overview ==
According to traditions such as the {{ill|Kiki|de|Kiki|ja|記紀|qq=draft}}, the clan is said to descend from {{ill|Emperor Kogen|de|Kaiser Kogen|ja|孝元天皇|qq=draft}}, with its founder being {{ill|Kose Komagari Sukune|de|Kose Komagari Sukune|ja|許勢小柄宿禰|qq=draft}}, the second son of {{ill|Takeuchi Sukune|de|Takeuchi Sukune|ja|武内宿禰|qq=draft}}{{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2310}}. After the 6th Century {{ill|6th Century|de|6. Jahrhundert|ja|6世紀|qq=draft}}, the clan emerged as a rising new power through its diplomatic and military engagements with the {{ill|Korean Peninsula|de|Koreanische Halbinsel|ja|朝鮮半島|qq=draft}}. Beginning with {{ill|Kose Otoko|de|Kose Otoko|ja|巨勢男人|lt=Man|lt_ja=男人|lt_de=Man|qq=draft}}, who became a {{ill|Minister (Ancient Japan)|de|Minister (Altes Japan)|ja|大臣 (古代日本)|lt=Minister|lt_ja=大臣|lt_de=Minister|qq=draft}} in the reign of {{ill|Emperor Keitai|de|Kaiser Keitai|ja|継体天皇|qq=draft}}, followed by {{ill|Kose Inamochi|de|Kose Inamochi|ja|許勢稲持|lt=Inamochi|lt_ja=稲持|lt_de=Inamochi|qq=draft}} in the reign of {{ill|Emperor Kinmei|de|Kaiser Kinmei|ja|欽明天皇|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kose Saru|de|Kose Saru|ja|巨勢猿|lt=Saru|lt_ja=猿|lt_de=Saru|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kose Hirao|de|Kose Hirao|ja|巨勢比良夫|lt=Hirao|lt_ja=比良夫|lt_de=Hirao|qq=draft}} in the reign of {{ill|Emperor Sushun|de|Kaiser Sushun|ja|崇峻天皇|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Kose Daimaro|de|Kose Daimaro|ja|許勢大摩呂|lt=Daimaro|lt_ja=大摩呂|lt_de=Daimaro|qq=draft}} in the reign of {{ill|Empress Suiko|de|Kaiserin Suiko|ja|推古天皇|qq=draft}}, members of the clan appear as officials of the {{ill|Daihu|de|Daihu|ja|大夫|qq=draft}} (councilor) class{{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2311}}, though their genealogical relationships remain unclear. In the {{ill|Asuka Period|de|Asuka-Zeit|ja|飛鳥時代|qq=draft}}, during the reign of {{ill|Emperor Kōtoku|de|Kaiser Kōtoku|ja|孝徳天皇|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kose Tokuda|de|Kose Tokuda|ja|巨勢徳陀|lt=Tokuda|lt_ja=徳陀|lt_de=Tokuda|qq=draft}} served as {{ill|Left Minister|de|Left Minister|ja|左大臣|qq=draft}}, and in the reign of {{ill|Emperor Tenji|de|Kaiser Tenji|ja|天智天皇|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kose Hito|de|Kose Hito|ja|巨勢人|lt=Hito|lt_ja=人|lt_de=Hito|qq=draft}} served as {{ill|Censorial Official|de|Zensor|ja|御史大夫|qq=draft}}; moreover, in the {{ill|Nara Period|de|Nara-Zeit|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kose Maro|de|Kose Maro|ja|巨勢麻呂|lt=Maro|lt_ja=麻呂|lt_de=Maro|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kose Eji|de|Kose Eji|ja|巨勢邑治|lt=Eji|lt_ja=邑治|lt_de=Eji|qq=draft}} held the position of {{ill|Chunagon|de|Chunagon|ja|中納言|qq=draft}}, while {{ill|Kose Neta Maro|de|Kose Neta Maro|ja|巨勢奈弖麻呂|lt=Neta Maro|lt_ja=奈弖麻呂|lt_de=Neta Maro|qq=draft}} was promoted to {{ill|Dainagon|de|Dainagon|ja|大納言|qq=draft}}{{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2311}}. In the early {{ill|Heian Period|de|Heian-Zeit|ja|平安時代|qq=draft}}, after producing {{ill|Kose Noashi|de|Kose Noashi|ja|巨勢野足|lt=Noashi|lt_ja=野足|lt_de=Noashi|qq=draft}}, who was first appointed as {{ill|Kurando-tō|de|Kurando-tō|ja|蔵人頭|qq=draft}} and later promoted to {{ill|Chunagon|de|Chunagon|ja|中納言|qq=draft}}, no other member rose to the level of court nobility. {{ill|Kose Kanaoka|de|Kose Kanaoka|ja|巨勢金岡|lt=Kanaoka|lt_ja=金岡|lt_de=Kanaoka|qq=draft}}, the founder of the {{ill|Kose School|de|Kose Schule|ja|巨勢派|qq=draft}}, was a great‑grandson of Noashi.

== Developments ==
* Early 6th Century – In the reign of {{ill|Emperor Keitai|de|Kaiser Keitai|ja|継体天皇|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Kose Otoko|de|Kose Otoko|ja|巨勢男人|lt=Man|lt_ja=男人|lt_de=Man|qq=draft}} became a {{ill|Minister|de|Minister|ja|大臣|qq=draft}}, and his daughters {{ill|Sadehime|de|Sadehime|ja|紗手媛|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kakayuhime|de|Kakayuhime|ja|香々有媛|qq=draft}} were married to {{ill|Emperor Ankan|de|Kaiser Ankan|ja|安閑天皇|qq=draft}}.
* In Year 2 of {{ill|Emperor Yōmei|de|Kaiser Yōmei|ja|用明天皇|qq=draft}} ({{ill|587 AD|de|587 AD|ja|587年|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Kose Hirao|de|Kose Hirao|ja|巨勢比良夫|lt=Hirao|lt_ja=比良夫|lt_de=Hirao|qq=draft}} participated in the {{ill|Teimei Rebellion|de|Teimei-Rebellion|ja|丁未の乱|qq=draft}} and annihilated {{ill|Mononobe Moriya|de|Mononobe Moriya|ja|物部守屋|qq=draft}}.
* In Year 5 of the {{ill|Taika Era|de|Taika-Zeit|ja|大化|qq=draft}} ({{ill|649 AD|de|649 AD|ja|649年|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Kose Tokuda|de|Kose Tokuda|ja|巨勢徳陀|lt=Tokuda|lt_ja=徳陀|lt_de=Tokuda|qq=draft}} became {{ill|Left Minister|de|Left Minister|ja|左大臣|qq=draft}}.
* In Year 1 of {{ill|Emperor Tenmu|de|Kaiser Tenmu|ja|天武天皇|qq=draft}} ({{ill|672 AD|de|672 AD|ja|672年|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Kose Hito|de|Kose Hito|ja|巨勢人|lt=Hito|lt_ja=人|lt_de=Hito|qq=draft}} sided with the Omi faction in the {{ill|Jinshin War|de|Jinshin-Krieg|ja|壬申の乱|qq=draft}} and was sentenced to {{ill|Exile|de|Exil|ja|流刑|qq=draft}}.
* In Year 13 of Emperor Tenmu ({{ill|684 AD|de|684 AD|ja|684年|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Kose Kuromaro|de|Kose Kuromaro|ja|巨勢黒麻呂|lt=Kuromaro|lt_ja=黒麻呂|lt_de=Kuromaro|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kose Shitan|de|Kose Shitan|ja|巨勢紫檀|lt=Shitan|lt_ja=紫檀|lt_de=Shitan|qq=draft}} were granted the surname {{ill|Asomi|de|Asomi|ja|朝臣|qq=draft}}.
* In Year 1 of {{ill|Tenpyō Shōhō|de|Tenpyō Shōhō|ja|天平勝宝|qq=draft}} ({{ill|749 AD|de|749 AD|ja|749年|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Kose Neta Maro|de|Kose Neta Maro|ja|巨勢奈弖麻呂|lt=Neta Maro|lt_ja=奈弖麻呂|lt_de=Neta Maro|qq=draft}} was conferred the Ranks of {{ill|Junior Second Rank|de|Junior Second Rank|ja|従二位|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Dainagon|de|Dainagon|ja|大納言|qq=draft}}.
* In Year 1 of {{ill|Kōnin|de|Kōnin|ja|弘仁|qq=draft}} ({{ill|810 AD|de|810 AD|ja|810年|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Kose Noashi|de|Kose Noashi|ja|巨勢野足|lt=Noashi|lt_ja=野足|lt_de=Noashi|qq=draft}} was reappointed as {{ill|Kurando-tō|de|Kurando-tō|ja|蔵人頭|qq=draft}}.

* {{ill|Kose Chūzen|de|Kose Chūzen|ja|巨勢忠善|qq=draft}} served the {{ill|Kishu Tokugawa Family|de|Kishu Tokugawa Familie|ja|紀州徳川家|qq=draft}}, and when {{ill|Tokugawa Yoshimune|de|Tokugawa Yoshimune|ja|徳川吉宗|qq=draft}} became shogun, they became {{ill|Hatamoto|de|Hatamoto|ja|旗本|qq=draft}}. Subsequently, {{ill|Kose Shishin|de|Kose Shishin|ja|巨勢至信|lt=Shishin|lt_ja=至信|lt_de=Shishin|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kose Shichū|de|Kose Shichū|ja|巨勢至忠|lt=Shichū|lt_ja=至忠|lt_de=Shichū|qq=draft}} (and so on) followed.

