'''Kose Clan''' (巨勢氏) is a [[:en:Clan|clan]] that adopts “Kose” as its clan name.

It was an [[:en:Ancient history|Ancient]] [[:en:Gōzoku|Powerful Clan]] based in [[:en:Yamato Province|Yamato Province]][[:en:Takaichi District, Nara|Takaichi District]]Kose District (巨勢郷) (present‐day [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]][[:en:Gose, Nara|Gose City]] Furuse (古瀬)){{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2310}}. The orthography of “Kose” is attested as '''Kose''' (許勢), , '''Kose''' (居勢), and {{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2310}}. The [[:en:Kabane|Surname]] was originally read as {{reading|[[:en:Omi (title)|Omi]]|o‑mi}}, and in the 13th year of [[:en:Emperor Tenmu|Emperor Tenmu]] ([[:en:684|684 AD]]), with the establishment of the {{ill|Eight Family Names|de|Acht Familiennamen|ja|八色の姓|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eight Family Names|qq=}}, it was changed to the surname [[:en:Ason|Asomi]]{{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2311}}.

== Overview ==
According to traditions such as the {{ill|Kiki|de|Kiki|ja|記紀|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kiki|qq=}}, the clan is said to descend from [[:en:Emperor Kōgen|Emperor Kogen]], with its founder being {{ill|Kose Komagari Sukune|de|Kose Komagari Sukune|ja|許勢小柄宿禰|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Komagari Sukune|qq=}}, the second son of [[:en:Takenouchi no Sukune|Takenouchi no Sukune]]{{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2310}}. After the 6th Century [[:en:6th century|6th Century]], the clan emerged as a rising new power through its diplomatic and military engagements with the {{ill|Korean Peninsula|de|Koreanische Halbinsel|ja|朝鮮半島|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Korean Peninsula|qq=}}. Beginning with {{ill|Kose Otoko|de|Kose Otoko|ja|巨勢男人|lt=Man|lt_ja=男人|lt_de=Man|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Otoko|qq=}}, who became a {{ill|Minister (Ancient Japan)|de|Minister (Altes Japan)|ja|大臣 (古代日本)|lt=Minister|lt_ja=大臣|lt_de=Minister|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minister (Ancient Japan)|qq=}} in the reign of [[:en:Emperor Keitai|Emperor Keitai]], followed by {{ill|Kose Inamochi|de|Kose Inamochi|ja|許勢稲持|lt=Inamochi|lt_ja=稲持|lt_de=Inamochi|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Inamochi|qq=}} in the reign of [[:en:Emperor Kinmei|Emperor Kinmei]], {{ill|Kose Saru|de|Kose Saru|ja|巨勢猿|lt=Saru|lt_ja=猿|lt_de=Saru|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Saru|qq=}} and {{ill|Kose Hirao|de|Kose Hirao|ja|巨勢比良夫|lt=Hirao|lt_ja=比良夫|lt_de=Hirao|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Hirao|qq=}} in the reign of [[:en:Emperor Sushun|Emperor Sushun]], and {{ill|Kose Daimaro|de|Kose Daimaro|ja|許勢大摩呂|lt=Daimaro|lt_ja=大摩呂|lt_de=Daimaro|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Daimaro|qq=}} in the reign of [[:en:Empress Suiko|Empress Suiko]], members of the clan appear as officials of the [[:en:Taifu|Daihu]] (councilor) class{{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2311}}, though their genealogical relationships remain unclear. In the [[:en:Asuka period|Asuka Period]], during the reign of [[:en:Emperor Kōtoku|Emperor Kōtoku]], {{ill|Kose Tokuda|de|Kose Tokuda|ja|巨勢徳陀|lt=Tokuda|lt_ja=徳陀|lt_de=Tokuda|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Tokuda|qq=}} served as [[:en:Minister of the Left|Minister of the Left]], and in the reign of [[:en:Emperor Tenji|Emperor Tenji]], {{ill|Kose Hito|de|Kose Hito|ja|巨勢人|lt=Hito|lt_ja=人|lt_de=Hito|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Hito|qq=}} served as {{ill|Censorial Official|de|Zensor|ja|御史大夫|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Censorial Official|qq=}}; moreover, in the [[:en:Nara period|Nara Period]], {{ill|Kose Maro|de|Kose Maro|ja|巨勢麻呂|lt=Maro|lt_ja=麻呂|lt_de=Maro|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Maro|qq=}} and {{ill|Kose Eji|de|Kose Eji|ja|巨勢邑治|lt=Eji|lt_ja=邑治|lt_de=Eji|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Eji|qq=}} held the position of [[:en:Chūnagon|Chunagon]], while {{ill|Kose Neta Maro|de|Kose Neta Maro|ja|巨勢奈弖麻呂|lt=Neta Maro|lt_ja=奈弖麻呂|lt_de=Neta Maro|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Neta Maro|qq=}} was promoted to [[:en:Dainagon|Dainagon]]{{Sfn|太田|1934|p=2311}}. In the early [[:en:Heian period|Heian Period]], after producing {{ill|Kose Noashi|de|Kose Noashi|ja|巨勢野足|lt=Noashi|lt_ja=野足|lt_de=Noashi|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Noashi|qq=}}, who was first appointed as {{ill|Kurando-tō|de|Kurando-tō|ja|蔵人頭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurando-tō|qq=}} and later promoted to [[:en:Chūnagon|Chunagon]], no other member rose to the level of court nobility. [[:en:Kose Kanaoka|Kanaoka]], the founder of the {{ill|Kose School|de|Kose Schule|ja|巨勢派|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose School|qq=}}, was a great‑grandson of Noashi.

== Developments ==
* Early 6th Century – In the reign of [[:en:Emperor Keitai|Emperor Keitai]], {{ill|Kose Otoko|de|Kose Otoko|ja|巨勢男人|lt=Man|lt_ja=男人|lt_de=Man|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Otoko|qq=}} became a [[:en:Minister (government)|Minister]], and his daughters {{ill|Sadehime|de|Sadehime|ja|紗手媛|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sadehime|qq=}} and {{ill|Kakayuhime|de|Kakayuhime|ja|香々有媛|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kakayuhime|qq=}} were married to [[:en:Emperor Ankan|Emperor Ankan]].
* In Year 2 of [[:en:Emperor Yōmei|Emperor Yōmei]] ([[:en:587|587 AD]]) – {{ill|Kose Hirao|de|Kose Hirao|ja|巨勢比良夫|lt=Hirao|lt_ja=比良夫|lt_de=Hirao|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Hirao|qq=}} participated in the [[:en:Soga–Mononobe conflict|Teimei Rebellion]] and annihilated [[:en:Mononobe no Moriya|Mononobe Moriya]].
* In Year 5 of the [[:en:Taika (era)|Taika Era]] ([[:en:649|649 AD]]) – {{ill|Kose Tokuda|de|Kose Tokuda|ja|巨勢徳陀|lt=Tokuda|lt_ja=徳陀|lt_de=Tokuda|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Tokuda|qq=}} became [[:en:Minister of the Left|Minister of the Left]].
* In Year 1 of [[:en:Emperor Tenmu|Emperor Tenmu]] ([[:en:672|672 AD]]) – {{ill|Kose Hito|de|Kose Hito|ja|巨勢人|lt=Hito|lt_ja=人|lt_de=Hito|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Hito|qq=}} sided with the Omi faction in the [[:en:Jinshin War|Jinshin War]] and was sentenced to {{ill|Exile|de|Exil|ja|流刑|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Exile|qq=}}.
* In Year 13 of Emperor Tenmu ([[:en:684|684 AD]]) – {{ill|Kose Kuromaro|de|Kose Kuromaro|ja|巨勢黒麻呂|lt=Kuromaro|lt_ja=黒麻呂|lt_de=Kuromaro|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Kuromaro|qq=}} and {{ill|Kose Shitan|de|Kose Shitan|ja|巨勢紫檀|lt=Shitan|lt_ja=紫檀|lt_de=Shitan|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Shitan|qq=}} were granted the surname [[:en:Ason|Asomi]].
* In Year 1 of [[:en:Tenpyō-shōhō|Tenpyō Shōhō]] ([[:en:749|749 AD]]) – {{ill|Kose Neta Maro|de|Kose Neta Maro|ja|巨勢奈弖麻呂|lt=Neta Maro|lt_ja=奈弖麻呂|lt_de=Neta Maro|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Neta Maro|qq=}} was conferred the Ranks of {{ill|Junior Second Rank|de|Junior Second Rank|ja|従二位|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Second Rank|qq=}} and [[:en:Dainagon|Dainagon]].
* In Year 1 of [[:en:Kōnin (era)|Kōnin]] ([[:en:810|810 AD]]) – {{ill|Kose Noashi|de|Kose Noashi|ja|巨勢野足|lt=Noashi|lt_ja=野足|lt_de=Noashi|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Noashi|qq=}} was reappointed as {{ill|Kurando-tō|de|Kurando-tō|ja|蔵人頭|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurando-tō|qq=}}.

* {{ill|Kose Chūzen|de|Kose Chūzen|ja|巨勢忠善|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Chūzen|qq=}} served the [[:en:Kishū Tokugawa family|Kishu Tokugawa Family]], and when [[:en:Tokugawa Yoshimune|Tokugawa Yoshimune]] became shogun, they became [[:en:Hatamoto|Hatamoto]]. Subsequently, {{ill|Kose Shishin|de|Kose Shishin|ja|巨勢至信|lt=Shishin|lt_ja=至信|lt_de=Shishin|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Shishin|qq=}} and {{ill|Kose Shichū|de|Kose Shichū|ja|巨勢至忠|lt=Shichū|lt_ja=至忠|lt_de=Shichū|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kose Shichū|qq=}} (and so on) followed.

